Question 49 The following function is defined over the interval [latex][-\mathrm{L}, \mathrm{L}][/latex] : [latex]
f(x)=p x^{4}+q x^{5}
[/latex] If it is expressed as a Fourier series, [latex]
f(x)=a_{0}+\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\left\{a_{n} \sin \left(\frac{\pi x}{L}\right)+b_{n} \cos \left(\frac{\pi x}{L}\right)\right\} \text {, }
[/latex] which options amongst the following are true?

solution:
[latex]
\begin{aligned}
f(x) & =p x^{4}+q x^{5} \\
b_{n} & =\frac{1}{\ell} \int_{-\ell}^{\ell} f(x) \cos \left(\frac{n \pi x}{\ell}\right) d x\\

& =\frac{1}{\ell} \int_{-\ell}^{\ell}\left(p x^{4}+q x^{5}\right) \cos \left(\frac{n \pi x}{\ell}\right) d x \\
& =\frac{1}{\ell} \int_{-\ell}^{\ell} \mathrm{p}\left(\mathrm{x}^{4}\right) \cos \frac{\mathrm{n} \pi \mathrm{x}}{\ell} \mathrm{dx} \\
& \left(\because q x^{5} \frac{\cos n \pi x}{\ell} \text { is odd function }\right)
\end{aligned}
[/latex] So, [latex]b_{n}[/latex] depends on [latex]p[/latex]. [latex]
\begin{aligned}
a_{n}= & \frac{1}{\ell} \int_{-\ell}^{\ell} f(x) \sin \left(\frac{n \pi x}{\ell}\right) d x \\
a_{n}= & \frac{1}{\ell} \int_{-\ell}^{\ell}\left(p x^{4}+q x^{5}\right) \sin \frac{n \pi x}{\ell} d x \\
a_{n}= & 0+\frac{1}{\ell} \int_{-\ell}^{\ell} q x^{5} \sin \left(\frac{n \pi x}{\ell}\right) d x \\
& \left(\because p x^{4} \frac{\sin n \pi x}{\ell}\right. \text { is odd function) }
\end{aligned}
[/latex] So, [latex]a_{n}[/latex] depends on [latex]p[/latex].

